Syntax (5): Compares primary and secondary datasources for equivalence
 mqsicvp --primary-datasource <arg> --primary-username <arg> --primary-password <arg> [--secondary-datasource <arg> --secondary-username <arg> --secondary-password <arg>] [--verbose] [--trace <arg>]
Syntax (6): Datasource benchmarking
 mqsicvp integrationNodeName [--integration-server <arg>] [--vault-key <arg> | --vaultrc-location <arg>] --check-type benchmark [--options <arg>] [--recursive] [--trace <arg>]

 Command Options:
 '--integration-node-name <integrationNodeName>' : Name of a locally defined integration node.
 '--integration-server (-e) <integrationServerName>' : Name of integration server, required when using vault and benchmark.
 '--vault-key <arg>' : indicates the vault key to be used to access the vault owned by the integration node or integration server.
 '--vaultrc-location <directory-path>' directory path for the .mqsivaultrc file used to locate the vault key and external directory vault key.
 '--primary-datasource (-n) <datasource>' : The name of the datasource to verify
 '--secondary-datasource (-c) <datasource>' : The name of the secondary datasource for comparison
 '--primary-username (-u) <username>' : The user identifier to be used to connect to the primary datasource
 '--primary-password (-p) <password>' : The password for the primary datasource username
 '--secondary-username (-i) <username>' : The user identifier to be used to connect to the secondary datasource
 '--secondary-password (-a) <password>' : The password for the secondary datasource username
 '--check-type (-b) benchmark' : Perform a benchmarking check. The only valid value is 'benchmark'.
 '--options (-o) <options>' : Options if Benchmark is selected. The first option for Benchmark will always be the test name. The valid test names are 'cpu-perf' and 'disk-io-perf'. Benchmark options:  cpu-perf,threads=[X],iterations=[X],sequence=[X].  disk-io-perf,numberoffiles=[X]  network-perf,ipaddress=[X]
 '--verbose (-v)' : Report additional diagnostics related to supported datasource CASTS.
 '--trace <traceFileName>' : send verbose internal trace to the specified file.


